cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.CG

The paper deals with algorithmic game theory, specifically mean-payoff parity games. This makes cs.GT (Game Theory and Decision Making) the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces new concepts such as strategy decompositions and progress measures, which are related to data structures (cs.DS) and logic (cs.LO). The algorithmic aspect of the paper suggests that it could also be classified under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) or computational geometry (cs.CG).
